statement:
Let $P \subset \mathbb N$ be the set of prime numbers
$P = \{2,3,5,7,11,\ldots\}.$ Determine whether the following statements
are true or false. Prove your answers (``true'' or ``false'' is not
sufficient).

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\textbf{(a)}
$\displaystyle \forall m \in P, \forall n \in P, m+n \in P.$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\textbf{(b)}
$\displaystyle \forall m \in P, \exists n \in P \text{ s.t. } m+n \in P.$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\textbf{(c)}
$\displaystyle \exists m \in P \text{ s.t. } \forall n \in P, m+n \in P.$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\textbf{(d)}
$\displaystyle \exists m \in P \text{ s.t. } \exists n \in P \text{ s.t. } m+n \in P.$
\end{description}
